    public abstract class CollectionNode<T>
extends ItemNode<T>
    A CollectionNode should always be used when the ItemNode is of type collection. Any collection do not need to be serialized into xml code (therefore methods Node.toXML() and Node.toPredictiveCodedXML(T iNode) are overridden

      • toPredictiveCodedXML

        public java.lang.String toPredictiveCodedXML(T iNode)
        Description copied from class: Node
        This method is used to create the corresponding predictive-coded xml output (on P-Frames). The data is not encoded like it is by P-Frames in pictures. The original Node will only be compared to this Node and all changed fields are written into the xml String (not the difference between the original value and new value!)
        Specified by:
        toPredictiveCodedXML in class Node<T>
        Parameters:
        iNode - the I-Frame Node which is used to create the P-Frame output
        Returns:
        the predictive-coded xml-representation of this Node or an empty String if data is equal
